02:23.289 --> 02:25.041
(sighs)

02:33.257 --> 02:35.426
(muffled screaming)

02:44.310 --> 02:47.188
(distant cackling)

02:52.485 --> 02:55.613
(buzzer sounding)

02:55.780 --> 02:57.824
(cackling continues nearby)

02:58.157 --> 03:00.284
(orderly humming)

03:03.121 --> 03:04.580
Merry Christmas.

03:05.623 --> 03:07.667
Merry Christmas
from your friends and family

03:07.834 --> 03:10.128
at the Clark Sanitarium.

03:14.507 --> 03:16.801
ORDERLY:
Merry Christmas.

03:17.176 --> 03:18.594
Happy holidays.

03:18.761 --> 03:21.723
PATIENT:
Leave me alone!

03:24.308 --> 03:26.728
Merry Christmas.

03:27.103 --> 03:29.564
Happy holidays.

03:30.565 --> 03:31.607
Happy birthday.

03:31.774 --> 03:34.569
Behold. Wise men from the east
came to Jerusalem,

03:34.736 --> 03:36.279
saying, "Where... "

03:46.664 --> 03:47.623
How'd you get in here?

03:47.790 --> 03:49.584
The door was open.

03:49.709 --> 03:51.586
I was looking for the children's
ward, and I got lost.

03:54.213 --> 03:56.466
GUARD : This ain't no place
for Santa Claus.

03:56.632 --> 03:59.135
Not at Christmas.

04:00.845 --> 04:03.681
(patient screaming in distance)

04:03.848 --> 04:05.600
Lenz?

04:05.767 --> 04:06.726
(door squeaking)

04:06.893 --> 04:07.769
Billy Lenz?

04:07.894 --> 04:09.896
That's the guy
that killed

04:10.229 --> 04:12.357
his family at Christmas,
back when I was a kid.

04:12.523 --> 04:15.318
You know, a lot of
people say he's dead.

04:15.485 --> 04:17.654
(squeaking)

04:17.820 --> 04:19.656
Poke your head inside.

04:21.658 --> 04:24.452
Check if he's been naughty
or nice.

04:25.453 --> 04:27.664
No, that's... it's okay.

04:27.830 --> 04:29.332
I thought so.

04:31.417 --> 04:34.420
You guys keep him locked
up with just a padlock?

04:34.587 --> 04:36.381
That lock's just to make him
feel at home.

04:36.547 --> 04:38.508
Right, 'cause
his mom kept him

04:38.675 --> 04:40.259
locked in the basement
his whole life.

04:40.426 --> 04:41.427
The attic.

04:41.594 --> 04:43.763
See, that's the key
to Billy Lenz.

04:43.930 --> 04:46.265
He just wants to feel at home,

04:46.432 --> 04:48.476
especially
on Christmas.

04:48.643 --> 04:50.770
He's tried to escape
every year...

04:52.730 --> 04:54.649
...just to be home on Christmas.

04:58.861 --> 05:00.697
It tastes like chicken.

05:02.323 --> 05:03.950
Because it's chicken.

05:05.284 --> 05:07.662
It's the closest
we could get to how

05:07.787 --> 05:09.706
Mom used to taste.

05:18.423 --> 05:20.341
Kyle...

05:20.508 --> 05:22.844
- Mm.
- It's late.

05:23.219 --> 05:24.554
I have to go inside.

05:24.721 --> 05:25.763
Mm-mm.

05:25.930 --> 05:27.306
- Mm-hmm.
- Mm-mm.

05:27.473 --> 05:28.558
They might be
waiting for me.

05:28.725 --> 05:31.769
("Dance of the Sugar Plum Fairy"
ring tone plays)

05:31.936 --> 05:33.563
See? That's them calling.

05:33.730 --> 05:35.940
You can be with them
any time.

05:36.316 --> 05:37.608
Yeah, but it's not
any time, though.

05:37.775 --> 05:38.776
It's Christmas.

05:38.943 --> 05:41.237
I know,
but it's our first.

05:41.404 --> 05:42.363
We should be together.

05:42.488 --> 05:43.448
We will.

05:43.614 --> 05:45.033
On Christmas Day.

05:45.366 --> 05:47.660
I can't wait until you
see what I got you.

05:47.827 --> 05:48.911
(both chuckle)

05:49.287 --> 05:50.913
And then, we'll be
together all week.

05:51.289 --> 05:54.500
Well, besides when
I have to work.

05:54.667 --> 05:57.503
Look, I'm excited,
baby, but I got to be

05:57.670 --> 05:58.838
with my sorority
sisters, too.

05:59.005 --> 06:02.508
I mean, I've never
really had a big family.

06:02.675 --> 06:05.678
I'm your family now.

06:10.600 --> 06:12.810
I love you.

06:12.977 --> 06:14.562
I'll see you later.

06:18.858 --> 06:22.028
(phone ringing)

06:24.947 --> 06:26.407
Hello.

06:26.574 --> 06:27.533
(jingle bells ringing)

06:27.700 --> 06:31.537
♪ I love
those J-I-N-G-L-E bells ♪

06:31.704 --> 06:32.997
♪ Bong! ♪

06:34.040 --> 06:35.667
♪ Jingle bells ♪

06:35.833 --> 06:39.295
♪ Jingle bells,
jingle all the way ♪

06:39.462 --> 06:44.509
♪ Oh, what fun it is to ride
in a one-horse open sleigh ♪

06:44.676 --> 06:47.011
♪ Jingle bells,
jingle bells... ♪

06:47.387 --> 06:49.347
WOMAN :
Billy.

06:49.514 --> 06:52.350
(sighs)
Billy.

06:52.517 --> 06:53.935
Billy...

06:54.310 --> 06:56.020
Girls, I can't find
Billy's present

06:56.396 --> 06:57.605
under the tree here.

06:57.772 --> 06:59.649
Come on, girls, we can't
start the Secret Santa

06:59.816 --> 07:01.609
without Billy's present.

07:02.652 --> 07:05.071
Hello? Who drew

07:05.405 --> 07:07.073
Billy's name?

07:07.448 --> 07:09.075
Um, Ms. Mac,
it's a Secret Santa.

07:09.409 --> 07:10.952
Can't we just get on with
this thing, so I can party

07:11.327 --> 07:12.620
for a few days
before having to deal

07:12.787 --> 07:14.414
with the family on Christmas.

07:14.580 --> 07:15.581
Have you looked outside?

07:15.748 --> 07:17.542
It's raining hail the size
of Yao's ball sack.

07:17.709 --> 07:18.918
It'll stop.

07:19.085 --> 07:21.546
The party gods won't allow me
to be here by myself

07:21.713 --> 07:23.423
- over Christmas break.
- Oh, I'll be here, Dana.

07:23.589 --> 07:25.466
Yeah, they're making me work
next week.

07:25.633 --> 07:27.969
That sucks... everyone
should be home for Christmas.

07:28.094 --> 07:29.846
All right, all right,
who's not here?

07:30.013 --> 07:31.097
Um, like everybody.

07:31.472 --> 07:32.682
Chelsea?

07:32.849 --> 07:33.975
She went home this morning.

07:34.350 --> 07:35.560
- Greer?
- No, that was her on the phone.

07:35.727 --> 07:36.978
She and Erin
and Taylor

07:37.353 --> 07:38.771
are off on that cozy
little ski trip

07:38.938 --> 07:40.565
with the boys
from G.A.D. next door.

07:40.732 --> 07:43.735
Didn't I see Clair earlier?

07:43.901 --> 07:45.737
Isn't she upstairs
writing a card to her sister?

07:45.903 --> 07:47.447
No, I think her sister
picked her up earlier.

07:47.613 --> 07:49.115
Remember, this
is the occasion

07:49.490 --> 07:50.783
for Clair and her sister
and her mom

07:50.950 --> 07:53.536
to... bury the hatchet
and rediscover

07:53.703 --> 07:54.495
each other.

07:54.620 --> 07:56.080
Oh.

07:56.456 --> 07:58.416
I'd like to bury the hatchet
with my sister...

07:58.583 --> 08:00.835
(dialing)

08:01.002 --> 08:02.462
...right in her head.

08:02.628 --> 08:04.130
(man cackling in distance)

08:14.390 --> 08:16.726
(patient yammering
in distance)

08:16.893 --> 08:19.687
(patient yelping
in distance)

08:20.980 --> 08:23.733
(patient shouting
in distance)

08:26.653 --> 08:29.489
(chair squeaking)

08:41.125 --> 08:43.669
(patient whimpering nearby)

08:54.931 --> 08:56.516
In your dreams, Billy.

08:56.683 --> 08:59.686
In your dreams.

09:09.654 --> 09:11.155
♪ ♪

09:19.872 --> 09:22.709
♪ ♪

09:32.927 --> 09:36.806
♪ ♪

09:52.071 --> 09:54.657
(girls giggling)

09:55.950 --> 09:57.535
Lauren, we're opening up
presents.

09:57.702 --> 09:59.162
(door opens)

09:59.537 --> 10:03.082
Clair, we're opening up
presents.

10:03.249 --> 10:05.543
Okay, I realize that
you're an only child,

10:05.710 --> 10:07.503
so let me explain.

10:07.670 --> 10:08.629
Christmas is
just Darwin.

10:08.755 --> 10:10.006
The weak get eaten.

10:10.173 --> 10:11.966
(pounding)

10:12.133 --> 10:13.593
We're opening up
gifts right now!

10:13.760 --> 10:15.595
If you're not downstairs
in five minutes, your presents

10:15.762 --> 10:16.554
are mine!

10:16.721 --> 10:18.639
(chuckles)

10:18.765 --> 10:20.808
Now show me.

10:20.975 --> 10:22.602
Okay.

10:24.604 --> 10:26.189
(pounding at door)

10:28.524 --> 10:30.818
We're opening up
presents in five minutes!

10:30.985 --> 10:31.944
If you're not downstairs,

10:32.111 --> 10:34.238
then I'm going
to take your presents.

10:34.614 --> 10:36.115
Just fuck Christmas.

10:36.282 --> 10:37.617
Fuck it.

10:37.784 --> 10:39.744
(softly) :
Whatever.

10:41.829 --> 10:44.165
Hey, Megan,
are you okay?

10:44.540 --> 10:46.876
Yes!

10:47.043 --> 10:48.836
(whispering) :
No.

10:49.003 --> 10:50.838
Megan...

10:55.635 --> 10:57.804
(sighs)

10:57.970 --> 11:00.056
LAUREN : Honestly,
Santa loves...

11:00.223 --> 11:02.308
(footsteps)

11:08.690 --> 11:10.692
(chair creaking)

11:12.986 --> 11:16.656
(panting)

11:22.829 --> 11:26.207
(clattering)

11:30.169 --> 11:33.673
(footsteps)

11:33.840 --> 11:36.718
(creaking)

11:41.931 --> 11:45.977
("Dance of the Sugar Plum Fairy"
playing)

11:46.144 --> 11:48.688
(creaking)

11:55.361 --> 11:57.322
(creaking)

12:02.702 --> 12:05.204
(clattering)

12:16.382 --> 12:18.384
(door creaking)

12:29.395 --> 12:32.231
(song continues)

12:40.156 --> 12:43.242
(playing "Dance of
the Sugar Plum Fairy")

13:07.684 --> 13:08.685
All right.

13:08.851 --> 13:10.895
Who's fucking with me?

13:22.365 --> 13:24.200
(song continues)

13:27.120 --> 13:29.247
Clair?

13:31.124 --> 13:32.375
What are you doing?

13:32.750 --> 13:35.461
(screaming)

13:38.798 --> 13:40.925
(muffled screams)

13:42.218 --> 13:43.928
(screaming)

13:46.347 --> 13:49.017
("Deck the Halls" playing)

13:49.183 --> 13:51.811
♪ Fa la la la la
Ia la la la ♪

13:51.978 --> 13:54.981
♪ 'Tis the season to be jolly ♪

13:55.148 --> 13:57.108
Hey, Santa, if I sit
on your lap,

13:57.275 --> 13:59.193
will you give me
what I want for Christmas?

13:59.319 --> 14:01.404
(chuckles)

14:03.906 --> 14:05.366
SANTA: I don't know,
you've been good all year.

14:05.742 --> 14:08.369
You sure you want to blow it
on the last day, huh?

14:08.745 --> 14:10.288
I'll be good.

14:10.455 --> 14:14.208
I bet you will.

14:14.334 --> 14:15.501
Happy holidays.

14:15.835 --> 14:17.211
- Yeah.
- (scoffs)

14:19.297 --> 14:21.507
Ever seen the backseat
of a sleigh?

14:21.841 --> 14:23.468
(door closing)

14:23.843 --> 14:27.513
♪ Fa la la la la la
Ia la la ♪

14:27.847 --> 14:31.017
You know, Santa
checks his list twice.

14:31.184 --> 14:34.937
I know you're
very, very naughty.

14:35.104 --> 14:36.022
Hello?

14:36.189 --> 14:37.857
WOMAN :
Santa, my shift's over.

14:40.151 --> 14:42.362
(chuckles)

14:42.528 --> 14:43.946
(slurps)

14:44.113 --> 14:47.241
You know, Santa's not one
to keep a girl waiting.

14:47.408 --> 14:48.910
(sharp thud)

15:09.055 --> 15:12.308
♪ ♪

15:16.854 --> 15:18.898
Mrs. Mac, why don't you
open the present we got you.

15:19.065 --> 15:21.442
Because we have to open
Billy's present first.

15:21.818 --> 15:25.113
It's a 15-year Delta
Alpha Kappa tradition.

15:25.279 --> 15:27.281
Okay, I...

15:27.407 --> 15:29.242
I drew that name.

15:30.368 --> 15:31.494
But can I say,
I'm sorry, I'm just,

15:31.869 --> 15:33.579
I'm really not okay
with any of this.

15:34.288 --> 15:35.623
I mean, buying a
Christmas present

15:35.957 --> 15:36.457
for a serial killer?

15:36.833 --> 15:38.292
MELISSA:
No, you see,

15:38.418 --> 15:41.462
serial killers murder
repeatedly for sexual thrill.

15:41.838 --> 15:43.423
Billy Lenz
was a spree killer.

15:43.589 --> 15:44.507
Dude just fucking lost it.

15:44.882 --> 15:45.591
Thank you.

15:45.925 --> 15:47.427
HEATHER: Oh, whatever,
Melissa, okay?

15:47.593 --> 15:49.095
I'm just offended
by a pagan sacrifice

15:49.262 --> 15:51.305
to ward off evil spirits
on Christmas.

15:51.472 --> 15:53.558
Heather, we're just having
a little bit of fun.

15:53.933 --> 15:55.935
Christmas is more about warding
off evil spirits than Halloween.

15:56.102 --> 15:58.062
What Christmas shit

15:58.229 --> 16:00.481
in this room resembles
anything Christian, huh?

16:00.857 --> 16:03.359
It's all
neo-pagan magic.

16:03.526 --> 16:04.527
Christmas tree...

16:04.902 --> 16:07.238
a magical rite ensuring
the return of the crops.

16:07.405 --> 16:09.949
The mistletoe is nothing
but a conception charm.

16:10.116 --> 16:11.117
Fifth century Christians

16:11.284 --> 16:13.453
jacked a Roman
winter festival...

16:13.619 --> 16:16.331
12 days in December
where the nights were long

16:16.497 --> 16:18.958
and the Earth was roamed
by the demons of chaos.

16:19.125 --> 16:21.377
And fucking Santa Claus?

16:21.544 --> 16:25.298
This fat voyeur
that watches you all year long

16:25.465 --> 16:27.050
to make sure you live up to

16:27.216 --> 16:30.136
his standards of decency before
breaking into your house?

16:30.303 --> 16:33.222
And that is different
from what Billy did... how?

16:35.099 --> 16:38.561
Billy didn't break in.

16:39.562 --> 16:41.564
Billy lived here.

17:00.917 --> 17:02.168
(puffing)

17:02.335 --> 17:04.378
<i>MS. MAC (voice-over):
Billy Edward Lenz was born</i>

17:04.545 --> 17:08.549
<i>with a rare liver disease
that gave him yellow skin.</i>

17:08.925 --> 17:10.550
Merry Christmas,
Billy.

17:10.926 --> 17:13.221
<i>His parents hated each other.</i>

17:13.346 --> 17:15.598
<i>The mother hated Billy.</i>

17:15.973 --> 17:18.518
<i>He was not the child
she always wanted.</i>

17:18.685 --> 17:21.604
<i>When she looked at her son,
all she saw</i>

17:21.980 --> 17:23.940
<i>was her husband.</i>

17:24.107 --> 17:26.358
(tapping cigarette)

17:35.702 --> 17:37.620
♪ ♪

17:40.456 --> 17:42.458
(ornaments rattling)

17:45.628 --> 17:46.713
(glass crunching)

18:09.485 --> 18:11.696
MOTHER: Why you bothering
putting with those cookies?

18:12.071 --> 18:13.740
Santa ain't coming to see you.

18:17.535 --> 18:19.579
Russians shot his sleigh down.

18:21.998 --> 18:25.460
Santa Claus... is dead.

18:34.594 --> 18:36.721
(whispering) :
Don't listen to her.

18:37.096 --> 18:38.556
Listen, if you go
upstairs to your room,

18:38.723 --> 18:40.141
you'll find something
for yourself.

18:40.266 --> 18:41.642
Now, go.

19:00.578 --> 19:01.621
(switch clicks)

19:12.548 --> 19:14.634
(grunts softly)

19:18.471 --> 19:20.598
FATHER: Look, I don't give
a shit if you're mean to me,

19:20.765 --> 19:21.683
but to your own kid
on Christmas?

19:22.058 --> 19:23.142
MOTHER:
This is my present to myself.

19:23.309 --> 19:25.353
I don't have to listen
to you no more.

19:25.520 --> 19:26.771
FATHER:
You didn't listen to me before.

19:33.611 --> 19:34.737
(door slams downstairs)

19:35.113 --> 19:36.322
FATHER:
Who are you?

19:36.489 --> 19:37.615
What the fuck do you want?

19:37.782 --> 19:38.491
MOTHER:
He's my family now.

19:38.658 --> 19:40.368
FATHER:
Get out of here!

19:40.535 --> 19:42.412
MAN :
She's mine now.

19:42.578 --> 19:43.538
FATHER:
This guy?

19:43.663 --> 19:45.623
This guy, this piece of shit,
is your boyfriend?

19:45.790 --> 19:48.209
MOTHER:
Gonna be my husband.

19:48.376 --> 19:49.460
FATHER:
Hey, what the fuck is that?

19:49.627 --> 19:51.170
I was in Vietnam.

19:51.337 --> 19:53.756
Do you think I'm afraid of
a dude holding a fucking hammer?

19:54.132 --> 19:55.174
No!

19:57.218 --> 19:58.678
(thud, Father grunts)

19:58.845 --> 20:00.471
(punch landing)

20:00.638 --> 20:02.640
(glass breaking, Father screams)

20:02.807 --> 20:04.684
(Father grunts,
punches landing)

20:04.851 --> 20:07.770
(glass breaking, loud thud)

20:08.146 --> 20:09.856
(dull thud)

20:18.156 --> 20:20.616
(breaths shuddering)

20:24.203 --> 20:27.248
(metal striking)

20:30.668 --> 20:33.671
(footsteps)

20:39.719 --> 20:41.596
(door opens)

20:47.268 --> 20:48.644
(man panting)

20:58.404 --> 20:59.405
(wallboard creaks)

21:03.242 --> 21:05.453
(scraping, digging)

21:16.255 --> 21:17.924
(both grunting, panting)

21:20.760 --> 21:23.346
(clattering)

21:26.307 --> 21:27.642
(gasps)

21:45.326 --> 21:47.829
(clattering)

21:51.791 --> 21:54.460
(object rolling)

22:05.471 --> 22:07.473
(phone ringing)

22:16.649 --> 22:17.692
(ringing continues)

22:20.278 --> 22:22.488
Alpha Kappa.

22:22.655 --> 22:24.824
Hello?

22:24.991 --> 22:26.534
Hello-hello.

22:26.701 --> 22:27.660
(chuckles)

22:27.827 --> 22:29.829
Very funny, Kyle.

22:38.004 --> 22:39.839
I think someone's in trouble.

22:44.677 --> 22:45.678
(beeps)

22:45.845 --> 22:48.348
(frantic breathing
over intercom)

22:48.514 --> 22:51.851
VOICE (imitating Mother) :
You want a Christmas cookie?

22:52.018 --> 22:56.397
You're my cookie,
and I could gobble you up!

22:56.564 --> 22:58.650
Billy, what have you done?!

22:58.816 --> 23:00.735
(sobbing) :
What have you done?

23:00.860 --> 23:01.944
(imitating Stepfather) :
Where's Agnes?!

23:02.320 --> 23:05.573
(imitating Billy) :
She's my family now.

23:05.740 --> 23:06.866
Hey, shouldn't
you get going?

23:07.033 --> 23:08.576
Don't you have lots
of toys to deliver

23:08.743 --> 23:09.661
- to good little boys and girls?
- Shh.

23:09.827 --> 23:13.873
VOICE (panting) :
Get out of my house.

23:14.040 --> 23:15.750
I'm gonna kill you.

23:16.584 --> 23:18.670
- Call the police.
- LAUREN : Please.

23:18.836 --> 23:20.755
Police ain't gonna do shit about
one wack-job phone call.

23:20.880 --> 23:22.048
Just dial "star 69."

23:22.423 --> 23:23.508
MELISSA:
That just calls him back...

23:23.675 --> 23:25.468
unless there's something
you need him to clarify.

23:29.514 --> 23:30.848
(beep)

23:33.434 --> 23:35.603
Caller I.D.
says Clair's cell.

23:38.898 --> 23:41.067
You really shouldn't
provoke somebody like that.

23:41.442 --> 23:42.735
What would you know
about dealing with anyone

23:42.902 --> 23:44.487
other than your
NASCAR daddy?

23:44.654 --> 23:46.364
I'm going home.

23:48.408 --> 23:49.909
Yeah, yeah,
run to Daddy!

23:51.828 --> 23:54.372
At least my family
wants me to come home.

23:54.539 --> 23:56.457
KELLI :
You guys,

23:56.624 --> 23:57.458
come on.

23:57.625 --> 23:58.751
It's, like, Christmastime.

23:58.918 --> 23:59.794
Yeah.

23:59.919 --> 24:00.837
Come on, Heather.

24:01.004 --> 24:01.838
What about your present?

24:02.005 --> 24:04.549
Give it to Billy.

24:07.635 --> 24:09.387
Merry Christmas,
Heather.

24:15.351 --> 24:17.061
Merry Christmas, everyone.

24:23.526 --> 24:26.821
You're all like my family now.

24:44.589 --> 24:45.506
Oh.

24:45.673 --> 24:47.133
Thanks, Eve.

24:47.467 --> 24:49.927
That's... that's so sweet.

24:51.971 --> 24:53.639
I know you like
the Bible and stuff.

24:53.806 --> 24:55.475
MS. MAC:
Well, that's the spirit!

24:55.641 --> 24:56.768
Well, come on, everybody.

24:56.934 --> 24:57.977
Let's get
this thing rolling.

24:58.144 --> 24:59.437
What have we got
here now?

24:59.604 --> 25:02.065
Oh! Melissa.

25:02.440 --> 25:03.149
There you are.

25:03.483 --> 25:04.150
And, uh...

25:04.484 --> 25:07.153
Let's see...
Dana, very nice.

25:07.528 --> 25:09.072
I wonder
what this could be.

25:09.447 --> 25:10.948
And let's see...

25:11.115 --> 25:11.949
Aw, "Mrs. Mac. "

25:12.116 --> 25:13.451
You shouldn't have.

25:13.618 --> 25:14.702
I'll open it later.

25:16.120 --> 25:18.831
("Carol of the Bells" playing)

25:21.125 --> 25:23.127
(grunting, panting)

25:26.881 --> 25:28.174
Not again.

25:28.508 --> 25:29.884
(grunting)

25:30.051 --> 25:31.552
(snoring)

25:31.719 --> 25:33.805
Every goddamn time.

25:40.520 --> 25:41.604
(snoring)

25:41.771 --> 25:45.108
(rocking chair creaking)

25:50.029 --> 25:52.573
(latch clicking)

26:01.082 --> 26:03.876
("Carol of the Bells" continues)

26:33.239 --> 26:35.908
MOTHER:
My little Agnes.

26:38.995 --> 26:41.664
(footsteps thudding,
chandelier tinkling)

26:50.048 --> 26:53.092
She's my family now.

27:01.726 --> 27:03.936
MS. MAC: All right,
let's get this party going.

27:04.103 --> 27:05.605
Um, let's see.

27:05.772 --> 27:07.815
This one's for Megan.

27:07.982 --> 27:09.859
Kelli, is Megan
coming down?

27:10.026 --> 27:11.819
All right, we'll save
that one for later.

27:11.986 --> 27:12.820
Uh... Oh.

27:12.987 --> 27:14.781
Here's one
for Mrs. Mac.

27:14.947 --> 27:15.865
Ooh, it's
a big one.

27:16.032 --> 27:17.825
(chuckles)

27:17.992 --> 27:19.619
All right,
I'll wait.

27:19.786 --> 27:21.954
And here is another
one for Melissa.

27:22.121 --> 27:23.623
It's a little one.

27:23.790 --> 27:25.083
Well, you know
what they say.

27:25.249 --> 27:27.168
Big things come
in small pa...

27:27.543 --> 27:28.711
Well, something like
that; I don't know.

27:28.878 --> 27:31.297
It's all right,
let's see what else.

27:31.631 --> 27:34.092
Then we'll open
the stockings.

27:34.258 --> 27:35.218
Oh, Eve,
wait, wait.

27:35.593 --> 27:36.594
Let me find
your gift.

27:36.761 --> 27:38.721
Eve...

27:43.059 --> 27:45.895
"To Eve from Santa. "

27:47.897 --> 27:50.066
Eve?

27:53.945 --> 27:55.363
Does Eve have someplace to be?

27:55.697 --> 27:57.240
The Island of Misfit Toys.

27:57.615 --> 27:58.908
Her mother was a legacy.

27:59.075 --> 28:00.159
And?

28:00.326 --> 28:01.577
Her mother's dead.

28:01.744 --> 28:03.079
She has no
boyfriend,

28:03.246 --> 28:04.205
no family.

28:04.330 --> 28:05.832
I mean, really,
where does she have to go?

28:05.999 --> 28:08.001
(footsteps crunching snow)

28:10.253 --> 28:12.130
Who hasn't gotten
a gift yet? Uh...

28:12.296 --> 28:13.798
Lauren?

28:13.965 --> 28:15.633
Just give her a shot of tequila,

28:15.800 --> 28:19.637
wish her happy holidays,
and she's good to go.

28:19.804 --> 28:20.972
Happy holidays.

28:24.851 --> 28:25.768
MELISSA:
All right, look, I know

28:25.935 --> 28:27.186
this is the whole
Secret Santa thing,

28:27.353 --> 28:28.855
but I know, um,
Clair drew your name.

28:29.022 --> 28:30.106
(chuckles)

28:30.273 --> 28:31.941
Oh, yeah?
She get me anything good?

28:32.108 --> 28:33.735
Oh, yeah.
It's a music box.

28:33.901 --> 28:35.611
(sighs)

28:35.778 --> 28:38.614
It plays "Dance of
the Sugar Plum Fairies. "

28:39.866 --> 28:40.950
Oh, fuck, no.

28:41.117 --> 28:42.702
I'm starting to see
the sugar plum fairies.

28:42.869 --> 28:44.746
I don't need to hear
the little fuckers, too.

28:44.912 --> 28:46.873
Language. Language.

28:48.791 --> 28:50.793
(wind whistling)

28:53.880 --> 28:55.256
WOMAN (over speakers) :
Wireless services report

28:55.381 --> 28:57.258
several microwave
relay stations are off-line.

28:57.633 --> 29:01.095
Now, a relay station sends calls
out of the area, so that is why

29:01.220 --> 29:04.098
your cell may work on local
calls, but not on long distance.

29:04.265 --> 29:05.141
Ooh-hoo-hoo!

29:05.308 --> 29:06.934
(laughter)

29:07.101 --> 29:09.812
Does it come with a man
to wear it for?

29:09.979 --> 29:11.439
(laughter)

29:11.773 --> 29:13.024
Whoo!

29:13.191 --> 29:15.401
Here is our real present.

29:15.735 --> 29:17.236
(phone ringing)

29:20.782 --> 29:23.159
I got it.

29:28.247 --> 29:29.999
Why is Megan calling here?

29:30.166 --> 29:31.668
(phone continues ringing)

29:32.710 --> 29:34.712
Hey, where are you?

29:34.879 --> 29:36.089
VOICE (imitating Mother) :
She's my family now.

29:36.255 --> 29:38.049
(imitating Melissa) : Everyone
should be home for Christmas.

29:38.216 --> 29:41.761
(imitating Billy) :
I'll be home for Christmas.

29:41.928 --> 29:45.890
I'm going to bury the hatchet,
in your head.

29:50.103 --> 29:51.437
That was not Megan.

29:56.150 --> 29:57.777
(speed-dial beeping)

29:57.944 --> 29:59.195
(line ringing)

29:59.362 --> 30:00.822
WOMAN (on answering machine) :
You have reached the main menu

30:00.947 --> 30:03.324
of Clement University
campus security.

30:03.449 --> 30:04.742
During the Christmas break...

30:04.909 --> 30:06.911
Is Megan in her room?

30:07.078 --> 30:08.788
I don't know.
I was just packing. What...

30:08.955 --> 30:12.041
What's going on?

30:15.128 --> 30:16.337
(Kelli and Heather screaming)

30:19.257 --> 30:21.467
(groans)

30:21.843 --> 30:23.845
KELLI (panting) :
Oh, my God.

30:24.012 --> 30:25.847
Kyle.

30:25.972 --> 30:27.765
What are you doing in there?

30:27.932 --> 30:30.435
I wanted to spend
the night with you.

30:32.103 --> 30:33.813
It's okay.

30:33.980 --> 30:34.981
KYLE :
And I knew that mama-san

30:35.148 --> 30:37.775
and your sisters here would kick
me out, so I-I tried to sneak

30:37.942 --> 30:40.445
into your room, but the window
wasn't open, so I, uh,

30:40.820 --> 30:42.780
I saw that,
I saw that Megan's was,

30:42.947 --> 30:44.866
so I climbed up here
to see you.

30:45.033 --> 30:46.492
Is Megan in
her room?

30:46.826 --> 30:48.494
I don't know.

30:48.828 --> 30:50.330
You climbed up
into her room,

30:50.496 --> 30:52.165
and you don't know
if she's in it?

30:52.332 --> 30:54.000
It's dark.

30:54.167 --> 30:55.752
LAUREN : Does he think
we're fucking stupid?

30:55.918 --> 30:57.503
You were in Megan's room.

30:57.879 --> 30:59.005
The call came from
Megan's cell.

30:59.172 --> 31:00.757
What call?

31:00.923 --> 31:02.008
MELISSA:
Can I just say,

31:02.175 --> 31:03.343
I'm sorry,

31:03.509 --> 31:05.386
but that-that fucking voice,

31:05.511 --> 31:06.888
that was not
Megan or Kyle.

31:07.055 --> 31:08.181
That was the fucking
devil, okay?

31:08.348 --> 31:10.475
And they were not
talking to us.

31:10.850 --> 31:12.143
They were talking
to Billy.

31:12.310 --> 31:14.437
KYLE : Billy Lenz, the guy that
used to live in this house?

31:14.812 --> 31:16.773
Well, you're definitely
getting punked.

31:16.939 --> 31:20.026
Yeah, Billy Lenz is
our fucking life.

31:20.193 --> 31:21.569
You know, you spoiled bitches,

31:21.903 --> 31:24.822
you come here for a couple
of years and you leave.

31:24.989 --> 31:26.908
I live here.

31:27.033 --> 31:29.327
I stay here.

31:29.494 --> 31:30.536
I used to play on this street

31:30.912 --> 31:32.789
before they turned them
into frat houses.

31:32.955 --> 31:36.042
This was the house that scared
the shit out of us,

31:36.209 --> 31:37.168
my whole life.

31:37.335 --> 31:39.504
What happened?

31:39.879 --> 31:43.508
You mean after he
washed down his...

31:43.883 --> 31:46.886
Christmas cookies
with a glass of milk?

31:47.053 --> 31:49.430
("Dance of the Sugar Plum Fairy"
playing)

32:19.377 --> 32:21.379
♪ ♪

32:27.844 --> 32:31.889
(squeaking)

32:56.914 --> 32:58.958
("Dance of the Sugarplum Fairy"
playing)

33:00.960 --> 33:04.464
MOTHER:
Merry Christmas, Agnes.

33:17.477 --> 33:20.146
(thudding)

33:24.275 --> 33:26.527
(whispering) :
Is that Santa's reindeer?

33:26.903 --> 33:29.447
There's nothing up there.

33:37.914 --> 33:41.376
Do you want a Christmas cookie?

33:42.919 --> 33:44.671
You're my cookie,

33:45.004 --> 33:49.509
and I could gobble you up.

34:02.689 --> 34:06.526
(tree rustling,
ornaments clinking)

34:06.693 --> 34:08.695
♪ ♪

34:12.364 --> 34:16.411
(gas hissing)

34:16.577 --> 34:17.578
(inhales deeply)

34:17.954 --> 34:20.706
(phone ringing)

34:25.712 --> 34:27.338
Merry Christmas.

34:27.505 --> 34:29.424
Merry Christmas...

34:29.590 --> 34:31.426
Hey. Merry Christmas.

34:31.592 --> 34:35.513
MAN :
She's my family now.

34:40.226 --> 34:41.686
(snoring)

34:42.061 --> 34:43.646
(weakly) :
Agnes?

34:45.398 --> 34:47.692
(stepfather snoring)

34:52.572 --> 34:54.699
(crunching)

35:04.000 --> 35:06.169
Billy!

35:06.336 --> 35:07.378
What have you done?!

35:07.545 --> 35:08.546
Where's Agnes?!

35:08.713 --> 35:10.631
Billy, where's Agnes?

35:11.007 --> 35:12.633
What your mother and
I must know is...

35:13.009 --> 35:15.094
Billy!

35:17.430 --> 35:18.723
Where's Agnes?!

35:19.098 --> 35:20.433
- (Agnes screaming)
- What have you done?

35:20.600 --> 35:23.478
- What have you done?
- (blows landing)

35:23.603 --> 35:26.230
(Billy growls, squishing sound)

35:26.397 --> 35:28.107
(Agnes screaming)

35:33.613 --> 35:36.199
(sobbing hysterically)

35:36.366 --> 35:37.450
(thud, record scratches)

35:37.617 --> 35:39.577
(sobbing hysterically)

35:39.744 --> 35:41.621
(electrical crackling,
Billy growls)

35:41.788 --> 35:45.333
(throaty gasping)

35:45.500 --> 35:48.628
(phone line beeping,
electrical crackling)

35:48.795 --> 35:50.171
(Billy growls)

35:51.172 --> 35:54.342
(blows thudding)

35:59.305 --> 36:02.100
(object clatters)

36:03.726 --> 36:07.730
(thudding continues)

36:14.737 --> 36:16.322
(squishing)

36:23.705 --> 36:26.833
(sizzling)

36:32.672 --> 36:35.675
(Agnes crying softly)

36:35.842 --> 36:38.302
(door creaking)

36:38.469 --> 36:40.179
Little girl in the corner,
she's hurt.

36:40.346 --> 36:41.848
Go check her out.

36:42.181 --> 36:44.475
(indistinct police radio
communication)

36:44.642 --> 36:47.645
(Agnes crying softly)

36:49.522 --> 36:51.691
(indistinct police radio
communication)

36:51.858 --> 36:54.569
(floorboards squeaking)

36:54.736 --> 36:57.572
(door slowly creaking)

36:57.697 --> 37:00.700
(indistinct police radio
communication)

37:03.328 --> 37:06.164
(crunching)

37:06.331 --> 37:08.750
(sirens approaching)

37:15.673 --> 37:17.842
(crunching)

37:18.217 --> 37:20.887
<i>KYLE (voice-over):
Billy was declared insane.</i>

37:21.262 --> 37:22.889
<i>They sent him away
to Clark Sanitarium.</i>

37:23.264 --> 37:25.391
(crow cawing)

37:25.558 --> 37:27.685
<i>Paramedics saved
his sister, Agnes.</i>

37:27.852 --> 37:30.271
<i>She lost her right eye.</i>

37:30.438 --> 37:34.400
<i>All scarred up, mother
murdered, an inbred.</i>

37:34.567 --> 37:38.655
<i>Her father, Billy,
who was her brother, Billy...</i>

37:38.821 --> 37:40.907
<i>a fucking psycho.</i>

37:41.282 --> 37:43.284
<i>They sent her to an orphanage.</i>

37:43.451 --> 37:44.827
<i>Like, what chance did she have</i>

37:45.203 --> 37:47.497
<i>that a foster family
would ever take her?</i>

37:47.664 --> 37:51.250
<i>No one's seen her since.</i>

37:51.417 --> 37:53.503
(rocking chair creaking
rhythmically)

37:53.670 --> 37:57.298
(wind howling)

37:59.801 --> 38:02.637
Did they ever
find out from him

38:02.804 --> 38:04.514
why he killed
his family?

38:04.681 --> 38:08.685
Well... it seemed to him

38:08.851 --> 38:10.937
that's how they showed
their love.

38:11.270 --> 38:12.522
(door slams shut)

38:12.689 --> 38:15.191
Clair?

38:15.358 --> 38:18.903
(drawers sliding open and shut)

38:19.278 --> 38:21.406
MS. MAC:
Megan?

38:30.832 --> 38:33.543
(clock ticking)

38:37.755 --> 38:39.841
Can we help you?

38:40.216 --> 38:44.470
She was supposed to call.

38:46.305 --> 38:48.599
I'm Clair's sister.

38:48.766 --> 38:50.435
Where is she?

38:50.601 --> 38:51.894
I'm kind of worried about Megan.

38:52.270 --> 38:53.479
Who knows
what her deal is, okay?

38:53.646 --> 38:54.814
- Can we go to my apartment?
- No. She was weird before.

38:54.981 --> 38:57.400
I mean, she was like a bitch to
me, and that's never happened.

38:57.567 --> 38:58.943
And we've been getting
these weird phone calls,

38:59.319 --> 39:00.611
one from her cell,

39:00.778 --> 39:02.655
and her car's still outside,
and she's just, what,

39:02.822 --> 39:03.906
gone in the middle
of this weather?

39:05.658 --> 39:07.327
- Hey.
- Ow.

39:07.493 --> 39:08.828
What, exactly,
are you looking for?

39:08.995 --> 39:10.663
Like, a note or something
that says she's okay.

39:10.830 --> 39:13.249
All her stuff is here,
and her car is outside.

39:13.416 --> 39:15.877
Okay. Call her cell.

39:16.252 --> 39:18.004
MS. MAC:
You're a legacy?

39:18.338 --> 39:19.756
What year?

39:19.922 --> 39:20.923
'93, '94, I don't know.

39:21.299 --> 39:22.342
I started late, I quit early.

39:22.508 --> 39:23.885
1993's the year
I became housemother.

39:24.010 --> 39:25.470
I don't remember you.

39:25.636 --> 39:27.555
I mean, this was supposed to be
such a big fucking weekend.

39:27.722 --> 39:29.724
Excuse my language,
but I drove

39:29.891 --> 39:31.642
all the way out here
in this shitty, shitty weather.

39:31.809 --> 39:32.810
I blew off a weekend

39:32.977 --> 39:33.811
in Vail with a
cardiologist...

39:33.978 --> 39:36.439
I love that coat.

39:38.691 --> 39:40.860
(phone beeps)

39:44.364 --> 39:46.866
Voice mail.

39:47.033 --> 39:49.494
(sighs)

39:49.661 --> 39:52.038
Meg, hi, it's Kel.

39:52.372 --> 39:56.417
Um, look, I was just wondering
if you were okay, and, you know,

39:56.584 --> 39:58.961
wanted to know what happened
to you and stuff, so...

39:59.337 --> 40:01.798
can you just call me back,
please, on my cell?

40:01.964 --> 40:03.716
Okay, bye.

40:03.883 --> 40:05.885
(phone snaps shut)

40:08.513 --> 40:11.516
(soft rustling)

40:19.899 --> 40:21.317
MS. MAC:
Clair's name is "Crosby. "

40:21.484 --> 40:22.402
This says "Colvin. "

40:22.568 --> 40:24.404
The divorce will
be final in March.

40:24.570 --> 40:25.655
What else do you need?

40:25.822 --> 40:26.781
Look, I can't tell
you any secrets

40:26.906 --> 40:29.617
about my sister, because
I don't really know her.

40:29.784 --> 40:31.577
I- I-I can't tell you anything
about this place,

40:31.744 --> 40:33.830
because I really fuckin'
hated it here.

40:33.997 --> 40:35.748
Um...

40:35.915 --> 40:39.085
I see Billy
still gets a Christmas present.

40:39.419 --> 40:41.587
Oh, this is new.

40:41.754 --> 40:43.047
It's not, uh...

40:43.423 --> 40:45.967
for Billy,
it's for Alpha Kappa from Billy.

40:46.342 --> 40:48.720
(clock chiming)

40:48.886 --> 40:50.888
That wasn't here before.

40:53.599 --> 40:55.685
Well, let's open it.

40:55.852 --> 40:59.647
(wind whistling)

41:09.741 --> 41:11.909
♪ ♪

41:13.953 --> 41:15.788
(gasps)

41:15.955 --> 41:17.582
What if there's something
on her computer, like, uh,

41:17.749 --> 41:19.584
an e-mail or something
that says where she is?

41:19.751 --> 41:20.543
Hey, you know what?
I don't...

41:20.710 --> 41:22.587
I don't feel comfortable.
uh, whatever, like,

41:22.754 --> 41:24.464
invading someone's
privacy like this.

41:24.630 --> 41:26.883
Try calling the
police again.

41:27.050 --> 41:28.634
(thudding)

41:28.801 --> 41:32.180
(scraping)

41:32.513 --> 41:33.598
Who put this
under the tree?

41:33.765 --> 41:34.599
She put it there.

41:34.766 --> 41:36.184
She found it.

41:36.517 --> 41:37.560
Are you actually giving me shit

41:37.727 --> 41:40.647
when none of you can tell me
where my sister is, huh?

41:40.813 --> 41:42.732
Where's her room?

41:42.899 --> 41:44.525
Well, you know what that is?

41:44.692 --> 41:46.694
The attic window's open.

41:46.861 --> 41:48.655
What, you think she's up there?

41:51.449 --> 41:54.577
LEIGH :
You know her better than I do.

41:54.744 --> 41:57.830
I'm her half-sister,
12 years older.

41:57.997 --> 42:00.083
Clair was in, um...

42:00.458 --> 42:04.545
I don't know, second grade
when I moved in here, this room.

42:04.712 --> 42:08.049
It's weird how, at this age,
12 years seems like nothing.

